  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the ASTER framework employs comprehensive static analysis to identify constructors, helper methods, private method call chains, and mocking requirements, providing a solid foundation for LLMs to generate high-quality tests [108].",
    "Furthermore, to handle languages with complex build systems like C++, frameworks such as CITYWALK extend static analysis to parse project build configuration files (e.g., CMakeLists.txt), extracting project-level dependency information such as third-party libraries and compilation environments [170].Code Simplification.",
    "Generating comprehensive tests for large, complex methods presents significant challenges.",
    "HITS [143] innovatively applies method slicing, a static analysis technique that decomposes complex methods into smaller, more manageable logical slices.",
    "This \"divide-andconquer\" strategy not only reduces the cognitive load on LLMs but also effectively improves the coverage of complex logical paths."
